// (Context, IERC165, ERC165, IERC721, IERC721Metadata, IERC721Receiver,
// IERC721Errors) flattened in above it so the file compiles standalone.
//
// The ERC721 contract body is the audited upstream source verbatim, with one
// deliberate omission: the tokenURI function. tokenURI is the sole consumer of
// the Strings -> Math -> Panic dependency tree (it calls tokenId.toString()),
// pulling in hundreds of lines of unrelated utility code. It is a non-critical
// URI helper the differential test never exercises, and gum has no uint->string
// conversion to mirror it, so omitting it keeps this fixture self-contained
// without changing the bytecode of any function under test. The concrete
// ERC721Mock at the bottom supplies a trivial tokenURI so it still satisfies
// IERC721Metadata, and exposes mint(to, tokenId) as the test entry point.
